---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---
<BaseLayout title="Privacy" description="MaaxGen privacy policy draft.">
  <section class="page-hero page-hero--accent">
    <div class="container prose">
      <p class="eyebrow">Draft for counsel review</p>
      <h1>Privacy policy</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        This placeholder outlines the intended privacy posture for MaaxGen. Review with counsel before public launch.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container prose legal-copy">
      <h2>Information we may collect</h2>
      <p>
        MaaxGen may collect information submitted through contact forms, booking forms, email, or other inquiry channels. This may include name, email address, business name, website, phone number, and message details.
      </p>

      <h2>How we may use information</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Respond to inquiries and schedule calls</li>
        <li>Understand the services a prospect may need</li>
        <li>Improve website content, offers, and communication</li>
        <li>Maintain basic business records and follow-up notes</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>SMS and mobile communications</h2>
      <p>
        If you provide your phone number and opt in through our contact form, MaaxGen may send text messages related to the consent you select (marketing updates and/or non-marketing messages such as appointment confirmations, replies to your inquiry, and account or service updates). Consent to receive text messages is optional and is never a condition of submitting a form or contacting us. Message frequency may vary, and message and data rates may apply. You can reply STOP at any time to opt out, or HELP for assistance.
      </p>
      <p>
        No mobile information will be shared with third parties/affiliates for marketing/promotional purposes. Information sharing to subcontractors in support services, such as customer service is permitted. All other use case categories exclude text messaging originator opt-in data and consent; this information will not be shared with any third parties.
      </p>

      <h2>Service providers</h2>
      <p>
        MaaxGen may use third-party tools for forms, booking, analytics, CRM, email, and website hosting. Confirm vendor names, data handling, and required disclosures before launch.
      </p>

      <h2>Analytics and cookies</h2>
      <p>
        If analytics or advertising pixels are added, this policy should explain what tools are used, what data they collect, and how visitors can manage browser or cookie settings.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Add the preferred privacy contact email and business mailing address before publishing.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
